info.headline: Flood Watch issued June 20 at 2:22PM EDT until June 21 at 12:00AM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT THROUGH WEDNESDAY EVENING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is possible. * WHERE...Portions of northeast Florida and northern Florida, including the following areas, in northeast Florida, Eastern Putnam and Western Putnam. In northern Florida, Central Marion, Eastern Alachua, Eastern Marion, Gilchrist, Western Alachua and Western Marion. * WHEN...Through Wednesday evening. * IMPACTS...Excessive runoff may result in flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - The National Weather Service in Jacksonville has issued a Flood Watch for Marion, Putnam, Alachua, and Gilchrist counties. Heavy rainfall of an additional 2 to 4 inches is possible, which may lead to flooding. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be prepared to take action should flooding develop.
